ServicePointManager.SecurityProtocol = SecurityProtocolType.Tls12;

Here's a weird one, it took me a while to get to the bottom of it:
It seems that when I have a UseBrowserLink middleware and start the project in Visual Studio with BrowserLink enabled, the `If-Modified-Since` header is removed from the request.

Here's a minimal repro:

```c#
public class Startup
{
	public void Configure(IApplicationBuilder app, IHostingEnvironment env)
	{
		app.Use((ctx, next) => {
			// it's OK here...
			Console.WriteLine("before BL: " + ctx.Request.Headers["If-Modified-Since"]);
			return next();
		});

		app.UseBrowserLink();

		app.Run((ctx) => {
			// ...but not here
			Console.WriteLine("after BL: " + ctx.Request.Headers["If-Modified-Since"]);
			return Task.CompletedTask;
		});
	}
}
```

The problematic request goes like this:
```
curl -X GET \
